Subject: Re: [T2] Test for fuel gauge on 76 bus

At 06:51 AM 10/16/2002, Vanagon man wrote:
>This bus I am working on has a dead fuel gauge..........I have added 3
>gallons of gas and it does not move.  I have taken the instrument cluster
>out, and all the wires are connected...................any way I can test
>it?

Fill it up before you conclude that it is totally dead.  Frequently the senders will wear through the resistor coil wire and not register on the lower half of the gauge.  At least then you will know it's just a bad sender.

-David
